# TypeScript Rules

## Type Safety
- Always explicit types, avoid `any`
- Use `unknown` when type is truly unknown
- Enable strict mode in tsconfig
- Use type guards for narrowing

## Types & Interfaces
- Interfaces for object shapes
- Types for unions/intersections
- Enums for fixed values (string enums preferred)

## Null Safety
- Use optional chaining `?.`
- Use nullish coalescing `??`
- Avoid non-null assertion `!` when possible

## Functions
- Explicit return types
- Arrow functions for callbacks
- Default parameters over undefined checks

## Generics
- Use for reusable type-safe functions
- Apply constraints with `extends`

## Async
- Prefer async/await over .then()
- Always try/catch async operations
- Use Promise.all() for parallel ops

## Imports
- Use named imports (avoid default exports)
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
